abstract: Ms. Warren got the most enthusiastic response of the 19 candidates who appeared Saturday. Bernie Sanders, Pete Buttigieg and Cory Booker also attracted particularly energetic support.
snippet: Ms. Warren got the most enthusiastic response of the 19 candidates who appeared Saturday. Bernie Sanders, Pete Buttigieg and Cory Booker also attracted particularly energetic support.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s backers roared supportive slogans and banged on drums as they awaited his arrival outside Southern New Hampshire University Arena. Senator Bernie Sanders was welcomed by die-hard fans ready to cheer seemingly every sentence he uttered. Mayor Pete Buttigieg and Senator Cory Booker delivered one applause line after the next.

abstract: Half of the Democratic candidates took part in a CNN town-hall-style event on global warming, and several unveiled detailed plans to address the crisis.
snippet: Half of the Democratic candidates took part in a CNN town-hall-style event on global warming, and several unveiled detailed plans to address the crisis.
lead_paragraph: A lot happened on the presidential campaign trail this week. Here’s our weekly catch-up on the 2020 election and the Democratic field, which is still 20 candidates strong.

abstract: Gov. Andrew Cuomo floated the idea of moving up the presidential primary, but legislative leaders were cool to it.
snippet: Gov. Andrew Cuomo floated the idea of moving up the presidential primary, but legislative leaders were cool to it.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY — The possibility that New York might consider moving its presidential primary to February rocketed through Democratic circles on Friday, potentially casting the state among a handful that will set the tone in deciding next year’s nominee.

abstract: The entrepreneur turned presidential candidate is explaining automation to the masses. And as voters realize he is serious and substantive, he is gaining a passionate following.
snippet: The entrepreneur turned presidential candidate is explaining automation to the masses. And as voters realize he is serious and substantive, he is gaining a passionate following.
lead_paragraph: PLAISTOW, N.H. — Meet Andrew Yang supporters and they often have a confession to make: When they first heard about Mr. Yang, they thought his plan to give every American adult $1,000 a month was a little crazy. But then, they will inevitably tell you, they heard him explain it, and it all started making sense.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates recently spoke of the need to address the adverse effects of global warming on poor and marginalized communities.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates recently spoke of the need to address the adverse effects of global warming on poor and marginalized communities.
lead_paragraph: The presidential candidates at the CNN climate forum on Wednesday repeatedly emphasized how climate change is hurting low-income communities and people of color, reflecting a growing awareness among Democrats that many of the problems they seek to address are inextricably tied to racism, poverty and other forms of discrimination and inequality.

snippet: Mr. Wohl, 21, a conservative operative who has promoted politically motivated conspiracy theories, was charged with selling an unregistered security.
lead_paragraph: Jacob Wohl, a conservative operative with a large internet following who has helped orchestrate efforts to smear opponents of President Trump, was charged this week with a felony in California related to the sale of a security, according to court documents.

abstract: We learned that there are some dividing lines on climate change within the 2020 field — and that young voters are asking some of the toughest questions.
snippet: We learned that there are some dividing lines on climate change within the 2020 field — and that young voters are asking some of the toughest questions.
lead_paragraph: Over a marathon seven hours on Wednesday, 10 of the Democratic presidential candidates participated in back-to-back CNN town hall events on climate change, fielding questions from audience members and several of the network’s top anchors.

abstract: CNN hosted 10 Democratic presidential candidates as they discussed their plans for tackling global warming.
snippet: CNN hosted 10 Democratic presidential candidates as they discussed their plans for tackling global warming.
lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of South Bend, Ind., framed his climate change approach at the CNN climate town hall Wednesday night as a moral imperative. “The real conversation we’ve got to have is about what’s at stake here beyond the traditional battle lines that have been drawn,” he said, mentioning national security and faith — an area where he has presented himself as particularly able to speak to conservative Americans.

abstract: Fighting climate change can create jobs, experts say, but politicians' estimates might not capture the complex reality of what that growth could look like.
snippet: Fighting climate change can create jobs, experts say, but politicians' estimates might not capture the complex reality of what that growth could look like.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic presidential candidates are rolling out their plans to fight climate change, and one thing is clear: Averting catastrophe is only one selling point. So far, nearly every presidential candidate claims that cutting greenhouse gases will also lead to an economic bonanza.
